THE LCL LICENSE (LEAVE CORE LICENSE)
Version 1.0

PREAMBLE
Traditional licenses prioritize the protection of "form"—source code, pixels, or strings of text. They impose rigid requirements for history, forks, and complex attributions. The LCL License rejects this obsession with the vessel. Instead, it mandates the protection of the "CORE"—the fundamental intent, the soul, and the philosophical purpose for which the work was brought into existence.

You are free to break the form. You are free to scatter the pieces. But you must never betray the Core.

1. THE CORE MANDATE
Definition of the Core: The Original Author shall define the "Core" of the work.
Grant of License: Any user, modifier, or distributor (hereafter "The User") is granted a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to use, modify, and redistribute the work in any form, subject to the following conditions:

Integrity of the Core: The integrity of the Core must be preserved. The work shall not be used in a context that contradicts, parodies in bad faith, or actively seeks to undermine the specific philosophical intent defined by the Author.

2. TRACEABILITY OVER FORMALITY
The User is under no obligation to maintain a formal "fork" history. However, the User must ensure that any third party can trace the work back to its Original Author. A single hyperlink, a source code comment, or a digital fingerprint is sufficient.

3. FREEDOM OF FRAGMENTATION
The User may disassemble the work. This license follows every fragment. As long as any part of the work is used, the User is bound by the obligation to respect the Core.

4. TERMINATION OF RIGHTS
If the User weaponizes the work against its own Core, this license is automatically and immediately revoked.
